data.text: Francis W. Lupton, Esq. of Potternewton Hall (died 1884) - great great grandfather of Michael Middleton (https://t.co/1KSHE1B6na) https://t.co/G39k1dopDn
"Nurse Olive Middleton, back row far right, in 1915 at Gledhow Hall, the estate of her cousin Baroness Airedale (https://t.co/oM9LoZj1vo) https://t.co/MmDBLrL11C
Apparently this is not image of Olive Middleton but of her cousin Baroness Airedale at the coronation of George V https://t.co/hgtEP13zYE

Olive gave birth to her first son, Peter Francis Middleton, in 1920, who was the Duchess of Cambridge's grandfather. 
He grew up to serve as Prince Philip's co-pilot during a South American tour in 1962.

It was there that Olive, alongside first cousin Elinor Lupton, helped save lives and participated in the advancement of women's rights – as a member of the first Executive Committee of the Leeds Association of Girls' Clubs.

As the Great War broke out. the turmoil unraveled, she volunteered to work as a nurse, offering her services at the estate of her second cousin Baroness Airedale – Gledhow Hall – which was also turned into a hospital for soldiers.
